{
  "doc_id": "14834",
  "text": "Among the approximately 200 Methylobacterium isolates that we obtained in our previous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , a sub-library of 77 isolates was selected based on their identity by WC-MS analysis (S2 Table) and subjected to screening. The library contains five eukaryotes and nine bacteria other than Methylobacterium species. They were selected based on their positions in the WC-MS dendrogram. They are considered to be unique to each other, and their 16S rRNA genes (or internal transcribed spacer [ITS] region) have been sequenced.",
